6 Customization
***************

All customization options are in the ‘autoslip-roam’ group:

     M-x customize-group RET autoslip-roam RET

6.1 Link Descriptions
=====================

 -- User Option: autoslip-roam-parent-link-description
     Description text for parent links.  Default: ‘"Parent note"’.

 -- User Option: autoslip-roam-child-link-description
     Description for child links.  If ‘nil’ (default), uses the child's
     title.

6.2 Headings
============

 -- User Option: autoslip-roam-backlink-heading
     Heading for parent links in child notes.  Default: ‘"Parent Note"’.
     Set to ‘nil’ to insert without a heading.

 -- User Option: autoslip-roam-forward-link-heading
     Heading for child links in parent notes.  Default: ‘"Child Notes"’.

 -- User Option: autoslip-roam-crosslink-heading
     Heading for cross-reference links.  Default: ‘"Cross References"’.

6.3 Behavior
============

 -- User Option: autoslip-roam-auto-crosslink
     Enable automatic reciprocal links when inserting cross-references.
     Default: ‘t’.

 -- User Option: autoslip-roam-sync-db-before-queries
     Sync org-roam database before queries.  Default: ‘t’.  Recommended
     for reliability.

6.4 Link Storage
================

 -- User Option: autoslip-roam-link-storage
     How to record parent and child references.  The value ‘'headings’
     (default) writes visible ‘** Parent Note’ and ‘** Child Notes’
     sections in the note body.  The value ‘'properties’ writes the
     references to a top-level property drawer instead, keeping the body
     untouched.  The property-drawer mode is useful in shared vaults
     where the visible heading noise creates merge-conflict surface.

 -- User Option: autoslip-roam-parent-property
     Property key used for the parent reference when link storage is
     ‘'properties’.  Default: ‘"FZ_PARENT"’.

 -- User Option: autoslip-roam-children-property
     Property key used for the list of child references when link
     storage is ‘'properties’.  Default: ‘"FZ_CHILDREN"’.

6.5 Reparenting
===============

 -- User Option: autoslip-roam-rename-files-on-reparent
     Whether ‘autoslip-roam-reparent’ and
     ‘autoslip-roam-reparent-subtree’ should rename each affected file
     on disk so that the filename prefix matches the new folgezettel
     address.  Default: ‘t’.

6.6 Chain of Thought
====================

 -- User Option: autoslip-roam-chain-heading
     Second-level heading written above a chain-of-thought outline that
     is inserted into a note.  Default: ‘"Chain of Thought"’.  Set to
     ‘nil’ to insert without a heading.

 -- User Option: autoslip-roam-chain-crosslink-heading
     Heading written above cross-linked chains-of-thought inserted into
     a note.  Default: ‘"Cross-linked Chains of Thought"’.

6.7 Example Configuration
=========================

     (use-package autoslip-roam
       :after org-roam
       :config
       (setq autoslip-roam-parent-link-description "↑ Parent"
             autoslip-roam-backlink-heading "Parent Note"
             autoslip-roam-forward-link-heading "Child Notes"
             autoslip-roam-auto-crosslink t)
       (autoslip-roam-mode 1))


