7 Commands
**********

7.1 Interactive Commands
========================

 -- Command: autoslip-roam-mode
     Toggle the minor mode.  When enabled, automatically creates
     bidirectional links for new notes with folgezettel addresses.

 -- Command: autoslip-roam-insert-next-child
     Create a new child note of the current note.  Suggests the next
     available address and prompts for a title.  Creates bidirectional
     links automatically.

 -- Command: autoslip-roam-add-backlink-to-parent
     Manually add bidirectional links between the current note and its
     parent.  Useful for existing notes or when automatic linking fails.

 -- Command: autoslip-roam-report-validation-errors address
     Interactively validate an address and display any errors.

 -- Command: autoslip-roam-diagnose-address address
     Diagnose issues finding a folgezettel address in the database.
     Shows all nodes and their extracted addresses.

 -- Command: autoslip-roam-check-duplicate-index address
     Check if an address is already used.  Warns if duplicate found.

7.2 Navigation Commands
=======================

 -- Command: autoslip-roam-goto-parent
     Visit the parent of the current note.  The parent is the node whose
     folgezettel address is one step shallower than the current one.
     Errors when the current note is a root.

 -- Command: autoslip-roam-list-children
     Prompt with a completion list of the current note's direct
     children, ordered by folgezettel, and visit the selection.

 -- Command: autoslip-roam-show-tree
     Open the ‘*Autoslip Tree*’ buffer, a read-only outline of every
     folgezettel-addressed node in the vault, sorted in canonical
     folgezettel order and indented by depth.  In that buffer, ‘RET’
     visits the node on the current line, ‘n’ and ‘p’ move between
     lines, ‘g’ refreshes the view, and ‘q’ buries the buffer.

7.3 Chain-of-Thought Commands
=============================

 -- Command: autoslip-roam-show-chain-of-thought
     Open the ‘*Autoslip Chain of Thought*’ buffer, which lists every
     ancestor of the current note from root to leaf along a single
     folgezettel chain.  The view shows only the connecting notes (not
     the rest of the subtree).  In that buffer, ‘RET’ visits the node on
     the current line, ‘i’ inserts the chain into the note that opened
     the buffer, ‘g’ refreshes, ‘n’ and ‘p’ move between lines, and ‘q’
     buries the buffer.

 -- Command: autoslip-roam-insert-chain-of-thought
     Insert the current note's chain of thought at point as an indented
     org bullet list.  Each bullet is a link to the corresponding
     org-roam node, and the heading above the list is controlled by
     ‘autoslip-roam-chain-heading’.

 -- Command: autoslip-roam-show-crosslinked-chains
     Open the ‘*Autoslip Cross-linked Chains*’ buffer.  For every note
     linked under ‘autoslip-roam-crosslink-heading’ in the current note,
     the command walks that note's own folgezettel chain and renders it
     as a distinct block in the buffer.  This gives the reader the
     context each cross-link sits in rather than just the link's title.
     Press ‘i’ in the buffer to insert all the chains into the current
     note.

7.4 Reparenting Commands
========================

 -- Command: autoslip-roam-reparent new-address
     Change the folgezettel address of the current note to NEW-ADDRESS.
     The command validates the new address, rejects duplicates, updates
     the title keyword, rewrites the parent backlink, and updates the
     old and new parents' forward-link sections.  When
     ‘autoslip-roam-rename-files-on-reparent’ is non-nil, it also
     renames the file on disk.

 -- Command: autoslip-roam-reparent-subtree new-address
     Like ‘autoslip-roam-reparent’, but also moves every descendant of
     the current note so that their addresses all shift to live under
     NEW-ADDRESS.  The command pre-checks for address collisions with
     unrelated notes and aborts without making changes if any are found.

7.5 Suggested Key Bindings
==========================

     (with-eval-after-load 'org-roam
       (define-key org-mode-map (kbd "C-c n c") #'autoslip-roam-insert-next-child)
       (define-key org-mode-map (kbd "C-c n p") #'autoslip-roam-add-backlink-to-parent)
       (define-key org-mode-map (kbd "C-c n u") #'autoslip-roam-goto-parent)
       (define-key org-mode-map (kbd "C-c n d") #'autoslip-roam-list-children)
       (define-key org-mode-map (kbd "C-c n t") #'autoslip-roam-show-tree)
       (define-key org-mode-map (kbd "C-c n h") #'autoslip-roam-show-chain-of-thought)
       (define-key org-mode-map (kbd "C-c n H") #'autoslip-roam-insert-chain-of-thought)
       (define-key org-mode-map (kbd "C-c n x") #'autoslip-roam-show-crosslinked-chains)
       (define-key org-mode-map (kbd "C-c n r") #'autoslip-roam-reparent)
       (define-key org-mode-map (kbd "C-c n R") #'autoslip-roam-reparent-subtree))


